==English==

===Proper noun===
'''Lavasan'''

# Lavasan is a city in North East of [[Tehran]], in [[Iran]]. Lavasan refers to two cities: "Lavasan-e-Bozorg" (whuch means Great Lavasan) and "Lavasan-e-Kochak" (whuch means Little Lavasan). Lavasan is a touristy and beautiful city, situated in north and north east of [[Latian]] dam. Lavasan is known as "beverly hills of iran", where you can find the most beautiful multimillion dollar villas of Iran, there. The most expensive neighborhood of Lavasan is [[Astalak]].